.TH timing_report_constraint_rise_fall_clock_period_check  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBtiming_report_constraint_rise_fall_clock_period_check\fR
.SH Syntax \fBtiming_report_constraint_rise_fall_clock_period_check\fR   {true | false} 
.P Default: false
.P Enables reporting of rise-to-rise and fall-to-fall clock_period checks separately for the report_constraint command.
.P When set to false, the software reports the rise-to-rise and fall-to-fall clock period checks under the same table in the report. With the false setting, when the report_constraint -check_type clock_period option is specified, the software reports violations that are the worst amongst all the rise-fall transitions for each point.
.P To set this global variable, use the set command.
.P
